  • Constructor Details

    • UIPage

      public UIPage​(@NotNull @NotNull UIBook owner, Object... constructorParams)

      Constructs a new UIPage using the specified Springable parameter.

      Construction Process

      1. Configures weaver() and ctx() implementations of this UIPage to return the values of the specified Springable.
      2. Uses the FxWeaver to load the controller for this UIPage using the definition defined by this UIPage implementation.
      3. Sets the UIPage of the newly-created UIPageController to this UIPage object. // TO-UPDATE - Move to internals
      Parameters:
      owner - The Springable containing the FxWeaver and Application Context required to construct and configure this UIPage.
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - If the specified Springable is null.
      NullPointerException - If the FxWeaver returned by this specified Springable is null.
      NullPointerException - If the ConfigurableApplicationContext returned by the specified Springable is null.
      NullPointerException - If the controller definition is null.
      NullPointerException - If the controller loaded by the FxWeaver using the controller definition defined by this UIPage implementation is null.

    • initializePage

      protected abstract void initializePage​(@NotNull @NotNull Object[] constructorParams)

      Initializes any unique components of a UIPage implementation.

      Details

      1. Called after UIPageController construction.
      2. Called prior to the controllers UIPage being set.
      3. Called prior to UIPageController.onPageBindingComplete()
      4. Parameter array should never be null.
      Parameters:
      constructorParams - The array of Objects passed to the UIPage constructor to be used to initialize/construct UIPage implementations.

    • controllerDefinition

      @NotNull protected abstract @NotNull Class<C> controllerDefinition()

      Abstract method that is to define the Class representing the UIPageController implementation to be used to define and manage the UI of this UIPage implementation.

      Details

      1. Used internally to automatically construct the UIPageController set to manage this UIPage.
      2. Automatic controller construction is done in the UIPage constructor
      Returns:
      The Class representing the UIPageController implementation to be used to define and manage the UI of this UIPage implementation.
